race.description: New Pakenham Gwm Opening Jan Handicap (62)
race.comment: TUSCALOOSA GEM (7) resumes looking well placed. She showed ability in her maiden campaign, winning her maiden here over 1100m at her third start. She profiles as a mare who will progress now and expect she takes catching. SMASH BLUE (6) is a handy sort who won her maiden fresh, good again last time in this grade at Cranbourne when just finding one better. She should be hard to hold out. FULLPROOF (2) resumes. Two runs last time in were solid and he has each way claims. STORMBOURG (4) has been below his best at his past couple but is better than that and his best rates well. DAPPER DON (3) next best.
